        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Prakash Surya",
          "email": "surya1@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2013-06-26 22:26:49.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-3504 ldlm: Don't kmalloc while holding spinlock",
        "message": "LU-3504 ldlm: Don't kmalloc while holding spinlock\n\nThis change fixes a regression introduced by the following commit:\n\n    commit 2c7a41a5c5958d36fa839ea91f3e63375cbd90fc\n    Author: Vitaly Fertman <vitaly_fertman@xyratex.com>\n    Date:   Tue Jun 26 01:47:50 2012 +0400\n\n        LU-1157 ldlm: replace waiting flock lists by hashes\n\nPrior to this fix, there existed a possibility to call kmalloc while\nholding a ldlm lock's spin lock. This is never acceptable behaviour\nbecause kmalloc may schedule, and we must never sleep while holding a\nspin lock.\n\nThis bug manifested itself on a production MDS via this call path:\n\n    PID: 24974 TASK: ... CPU: 19 COMMAND: \"mdt02_010\"\n     #0 [...] schedule\n     #1 [...] __cond_resched+0x2a at ...\n     #2 [...] _cond_resched+0x30 at ...\n     #3 [...] __kmalloc+0x130 at ...\n     #4 [...] cfs_alloc+0x30 at ... [libcfs]\n     #5 [...] cfs_hash_create+0x151 at ... [libcfs]\n     #6 [...] ldlm_init_flock_export+0x54 at ... [ptlrpc]\n     #7 [...] ldlm_process_flock_lock+0x1432 at ... [ptlrpc]\n     #8 [...] ldlm_lock_enqueue+0x405 at ... [ptlrpc]\n     #9 [...] ldlm_handle_enqueue0+0x4ef at ... [ptlrpc]\n    #10 [...] mdt_enqueue+0x46 at ... [mdt]\n    #11 [...] mdt_handle_common+0x648 at ... [mdt]\n    #12 [...] mdt_regular_handle+0x15 at ... [mdt]\n    #13 [...] ptlrpc_server_handle_request+0x398 at ... [ptlrpc]\n    #14 [...] ptlrpc_main+0xace at ... [ptlrpc]\n    #15 [...] child_rip+0xa at ...\n\nTo fix this scenario, the call to ldlm_init_flock_export() initializing\nthe exp_flock_hash field was removed from ldlm_flock_blocking_link(),\nand into ldlm_init_export().\n\nSigned-off-by: Prakash Surya <surya1@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: Ieb703d7a4bf913ea3541bd421a7d553137aba34d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
